Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["I. Setup", "Chapter",
 CellFrame->{{0, 0}, {0, 0}},
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992920100052187*^9, 3.992920108101376*^9}, {
   3.992920497984243*^9, 3.9929205385169573`*^9}, 
   3.992922712466095*^9},ExpressionUUID->"f3002120-159a-4588-9240-\
7ae6731e7278"],

Cell["\<\
In this chapter the necessary preparation is done to create the continued \
fraction equation in the following section. Every parameter is first \
expressed exclusively in terms of the horizons r_+ and r_C (L=1) following \
thesis section 2.1. These are then expanded in terms of \[Eta] = (r_C - \
r_+)/L = r_C - r_+. Finally, auxiliary functions are defined, which \
conveniently expand any quantity in terms of \[Eta] up to expansionOrder, \
with coefficients exclusively parametrized in r_+.

The most challenging part in obtaining the expansion for \[Nu] is the fact \
that the expressions obtained, even at intermediate steps, quickly get \
bloated. For this reason, this code tries to implement a delicate balance \
between early and aggressive simplifications, and acceptable runtimes of the \
notebook. Achieving this balance has been the main challenge throughout this \
part of the thesis and thus, in the eyes of the author, represents the main \
contribution of the this code. This is further the reason why throughout the \
code, byte- and leafcounts are repeatedly displayed; we keep this to \
facilitate future debugging. \
\>", "Text",
 CellFrame->{{0, 0}, {0, 0}},
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9929205592046947`*^9, 3.992920946092009*^9}, {
  3.992921009777926*^9, 3.9929210652948933`*^9}, {3.9929212080872803`*^9, 
  3.992921253268866*^9}, {3.9929229936073847`*^9, 
  3.992922994378961*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b9fb8514-ee75-44b1-9f17-\
25c6726c7292"],

